title: Lamamra holds a working session with his Maltese counterpart
text: At the end of the fifth Paris Peace Forum, held in the French capital, the minister of Foreign Affairs and National Community Abroad, Ramtane Lamamra held discussions with Borg, tackling the bilateral relations between Algeria and Malta in various areas and the ways to strengthen and raise them to the level of the historical friendship ties between the two countries.
The two sides also discussed the security, political and economic issues at both regional and international levels.

The two ministers agreed on the need to intensify consultation and coordination between the diplomats of the two countries, at the level of organizations and cooperation frameworks, like the Euro-Mediterranean Partnership, the Group 5+5 and the United Nations.
